author: Matthew Frank
comment: The Android app is substantially better than the Windows app or the web app.  It requires relogin too frequently, and has a few other annoying popups that interrupt quickly joining and leaving meetings.  (Like the persistent requests to rate the app).  It can automatically join audio, which is nice, but doesn't handle different connectivity conditions smoothly (assumes you always are logged into wifi).

author: Brian Kleyn
comment: Everything was fine until I received a phone call. After the call ended, the sound went very muted and I had to keep my ear next to the speaker to follow the conversation. Fortunately, it was question period so nothing visual had to be followed

author: Apoorv Agarwal
comment: The main problem I faced was that even though meetings are there on my calendar,  some recurring ones don't show up in the mobile app. Not sure if recurring ones need some special settings or something.

Absolutely horrible. Works one week. Fails the next. Volume is so soft I cannot understand it even if held near my ear with volume on 100%. No features. Webex has no meaningful support for Linux desktop. Ugh.

author: Kranthi Kumar
comment: Sharing access is not supported on mobile. Joined a meeting and wanted control the host pc for some navigation purpose, but unable to request access at the same time host could not provide me the control to access. Is this a limitation or restriction. In other terms great app.

author: G Douthett
comment: I had 3 parties on call and we had to end call and call on our cell phones because we could not hear each other.  I feel like I've paid for nothing. Even the chat did not work!

author: Benjamin Almarza
comment: It didn't work with Linux , it didn't work in any android's browser, my last hope was the app and it failed me. I will prefer to use anything else, Skype , GoToMeeting, Whatapp.

author: dauhuan
comment: My team is in southern California and I'm in Illinois. If it was for webex, long distant thing wouldn't work.

author: Kesharan Moodley
comment: I was late for a meeting, and I was having such difficulty with my pc. Downloaded this app under a min, clicked my meeting link and Presto.... worked like a charm. Thank you!!

author: Pete Amundson
comment: Overall the meeting experience is good. However, if you don't want the app to access or update your calendars or contacts, it will continually prompt and re-prompt with an overly that is extremely ignorant of your users desires.

author: FN TAYLOR
comment: When launched from an appointment in Microsoft Outlook this APP runs from within that application, effectively preventing any use of Outlook while WebEx meeting is in session. Contacts, Notes, emails, etc. are inaccessible unless WebEx session is stopped. Very limiting!!

author: Nishant Saran
comment: It requires 2 step verification all the time. Why should an app once authenticated require 2 step verification? I can't tell you number of times I have been late to meetings because the app decided it's time to do two step verification. This app is running on my phone that is syncing all my email and other corporate data and has my company's MDM. This is the only app which doesn't remember that I have used this app on the same device and used two factor authentication hundreds of time. Such a useless piece of garbage.   Oh and don't get me started  on what a resource hog this is... Drains my brand new Pixel 2 battery. But shouldn't be surprised WebEx on PC is a resource hog bloated piece of software as well.   Just plain terrible product.

author: Verna Smith
comment: Best meeting app I've used so far. So much better than dial in teleconferencing it's ridiculous.

author: Fred Arce
comment: Works well for meetings, can be slow with many participants,  where audio gets choppy. It also doesn't seem to adjust bit rate under poor connection quality causing breaks in what is said and heard

author: Olivia Wills
comment: Since the recent update I'm unable to  use the speaker function for meetings when connecting through the internet. Huge problem please fix ASAP.

author: Saqib Sabir
comment: Found it really handy to attend meetings on the go or away from the PC. For screen sharing it's pretty good. Haven't tried audio yet as I dial in separately.

author: Michael Thompson
comment: Biggest complaint is it does not remember previously entered addresses. That would get a 5 star.

author: Chris Morrison
comment: Does what it needs to do and easy to install and use. I did not see am immediately intuitive way to maximize my own video feed to ensure others had a clear view of me and my context,  but otherwise a great app. Saved me from taking a half day at the office!

author: Edward Walcott
comment: I can see everything but there is no volume, even when I put headphones in. It's annoying I missed a whole class because of it. It's not user Friendly enough to show me the steps how to turn the volume on!

author: Bengt Grønås
comment: It shows desktop ok. Voip is a dissapointment. Zoom is a much better tool

author: Robert Talbert
comment: Complete failure to work on a Chromebook. Neither this app nor the Chrome app nor the website allows me to join a meeting on my Chromebook Pro. In fact in instucts me to "use a computer instead" which I find somewhat insulting.

author: Ibn Batuta
comment: Video and audio setup rather clumsy, difficult to maintain settings duri.g ongoing conference call and worst of all, each time a member w/o video speaks all are w/o video.

author: charlotte ambele
comment: I use it for school and find it easier to use than the desktop version. We used blackboard collaborate before and I could not login with the app through my school. Love the fact that I don't have to be sitting somewhere to attend a class. Can zoom the screen in and out
Could hear everyone but I couldn't speak and I can only year everyone after I called a number they gave me. Maybe next time I will not call on the internet.

author: Bunny Charles
comment: You can take the call and view shared screens all on the go, thanks to this app. Works well even with mobile data (4G). 👍 Saves the day when you don't have any other way!👌

author: Sowmya J
comment: Webex meetings on the go with all options similar the one you see on the desktop app, what else would I want ? I like this app and would wait to see it upgrade unimaginably

author: Wildthing Mk
comment: The volume could have been more loud. Other than the volume the app is great

author: Kausik Chakrabarti
comment: This is outstanding app. Just eliminating the use if laptop for even serious meetings.

author: Anup Nayak
comment: Wish they stored a list of recent meetings I joined. It would be less of a hassle entering details  of meetings I regularly attend.

author: Ma. Aurora Carla Ortiz
comment: Some content/webinars are not supported ex no visuals or audio tho i dont know if it is device related or not

author: Xavier McKinzie
comment: The latest update removed my ability to merge a 3 way conference call.  I had to u install until that is resolved.   ****This works much better on my Nexus 5 and I have no issues with it.

author: Jeevan Vijay
comment: Always facing issues with the audio. Both in windows machine and android app. Audio is low. It doesn't connect to the external speaker. Always the speaker from the device.
App does not allow you to join by entering the meeting number. Says the meeting number is not recognized. Must join by a link or by entering a URL

author: Balaji Srinivasan
comment: Unable to share my screen through iPad. Not sure if I am missing something

author: Sandeep Balasubramanyam
comment: Audio output is to low making it practically unusable. If you fix it it's a 5 from my side.

author: Rim B
comment: Could not get this thing to work on my phone. No audio. No video. Just text saying who was talking...

author: Meredith Metz
comment: It'd be beneficial if I didn't have to enter my credentials each time, perhaps a fingerprint login, but I do find it very easy to use!

author: Curtis Keller
comment: Works for me.     I use it regularly to join meetings on the go.    Have a good  cellular data  plan or stick with  Wi-Fi.

author: Mr James
comment: Works as expected.  Can view screencast and conference in over WiFi.   Solid performance on my 2 years old phone. A real lifesaver for conferencing in airports and train stations!
Very simple interface however the sound went digital several times and there was no video...(perhaps it was an audio only meeting?)
